  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><em>The Hotel Village has a central location in the resort, and the spacious rooms and proximity to the children’s clubs makes it a great choice for families.</em></p>
<p><strong>Classic Cottages</strong> measure about 20-22m² and are set amongst the verdant Mediterranean gardens. Most are on the upper floor and have a window overlooking the village (it’s possible to upgrade to a room with a balcony for a supplement). These rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><strong>Garden Cottages</strong> are about 21-25m² and are set on the ground floor and come with a small, private garden that’s furnished with a table and chairs. These rooms sleep  up to 3 people in double or twin beds, with an extra bed or cot available on request. These rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><strong>Superior Cottages</strong> offer a bright, sunny space with large patio doors leading onto a private garden. They have a bit more space at 21-25m² and sleep up to 3 people in double or twin beds, with an extra bed or cot available on request. These rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><strong>Family Classic Cottages</strong> measure about 20-22m² and sleep up to four people with two separated sleeping areas on the same level and one bathroom. Extra baby cots are available on request.</p>
<p><strong>Family Garden Cottages </strong>measure about 40m² have a mezzanine floor for the second bedroom. They are in a central position and have a shared garden. These rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><strong>Family Superior Cottages</strong> have a mezzanine floor for the second bedroom and private furnished gardens – the Superior cottages also come with a second bathroom. These rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>]]></roomsDescription>
